{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DimqXp4JMZuAnP1BLHUN3i","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me compile the comprehensive findings:\n\n## Summary: Project Conventions for Implementing Fitness Evaluation\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here are the key conventions and patterns you should follow:\n\n### 1. **Module Name and Imports**\n- **Module:** `github.com/cloche-dev/cloche`\n- **Go version:** 1.25.3\n- **Standard test assertion library:** `github.com/stretchr/testify` (both `assert` and `require`)\n\nFile: `/workspace/go.mod`\n\n### 2. **domain.Run Type Definition**\nLocation: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Core fields:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string                // unique run identifier\n    WorkflowName   string                // which workflow was executed\n    State          RunState               // pending|running|succeeded|failed|cancelled\n    ActiveSteps    []string               // currently executing steps\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution       // complete execution history\n    StartedAt      time.Time              // when run began\n    CompletedAt    time.Time              // when run finished\n    ProjectDir     string                 // project directory path\n    ErrorMessage   string                 // failure reason if State==failed\n    ContainerID    string                 // docker container ID if containerized\n    BaseSHA        string                 // git HEAD SHA at run start\n    ContainerKept  bool                   // retention flag\n    Title          string                 // one-line summary\n    IsHost         bool                   // true for host workflow runs\n    ParentRunID    string                 // parent run ID if child run\n    TaskID         string                 // optional task association\n}\n```\n\n**Key methods:**\n- `NewRun(id, workflowName)` - factory function\n- `Start()` - marks run as running, sets StartedAt\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)` - adds to ActiveSteps and StepExecutions\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` - transitions step to completed\n- `Complete(state)` - marks run terminal with given state\n- `Fail(msg)` - marks run failed with error message\n- `FindFirstFailedStep()` - returns first step with fail/error result\n- `ActiveStepsString()` / `SetActiveStepsFromString()` - serialization helpers\n\n### 3. **Existing Evolution Files Structure**\nLocation: `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n\n**Key files already present:**\n- `types.go` - Core evolution domain types (see below)\n- `collector.go` - Gathers runs, captures, knowledge base, and prompts\n- `classifier.go` - Categorizes runs (bug|feedback|feature|enhancement|chore)\n- `reflector.go` - Extracts lessons from execution traces\n- `curator.go` - Applies lessons to prompts\n- `scriptgen.go` - Generates new scripts\n- `audit.go` - Logs evolution actions and manages JSONL files\n- `llmclient.go` - LLM interface\n- `orchestrator.go` - Wires all stages together\n- `trigger.go` - Determines when to trigger evolution\n- `evolution_test.go` - Comprehensive test suite\n\n**Core types from types.go:**\n```go\ntype CollectedData struct {\n    Runs            []*domain.Run                      // past runs\n    Captures        map[string][]*domain.StepExecution // run_id -> captures\n    KnowledgeBase   string                             // JSONL content\n    CurrentPrompts  map[string]string                  // relative path -> content\n    CurrentWorkflow string                             // .cloche file content\n    WorkflowPath    string                             // path to .cloche file\n    ProjectDir      string\n    WorkflowName    string\n}\n\ntype Lesson struct {\n    ID              string   `json:\"id\"`\n    Category        string   `json:\"category\"`           // prompt_improvement|new_step\n    StepType        string   `json:\"step_type,omitempty\"` // script|agent for new_step\n    Target          string   `json:\"target,omitempty\"`   // file to update\n    Insight         string   `json:\"insight\"`            // pattern observed\n    SuggestedAction string   `json:\"suggested_action\"`   // concrete change\n    Evidence        []string `json:\"evidence\"`           // run IDs supporting this\n    Confidence      string   `json:\"confidence\"`         // high|medium|low\n}\n\ntype EvolutionResult struct {\n    ID             string   `json:\"id\"`\n    ProjectDir     string   `json:\"project_dir\"`\n    WorkflowName   string   `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n    TriggerRunID   string   `json:\"trigger_run_id\"`\n    Timestamp      string   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n    Classification string   `json:\"classification\"`\n    Changes        []Change `json:\"changes\"`\n    KnowledgeDelta string   `json:\"knowledge_delta\"`\n}\n\ntype Change struct {\n    Type     string `json:\"type\"`     // prompt_update|add_script|add_step\n    File     string `json:\"file\"`\n    Reason   string `json:\"reason\"`\n    Snapshot string `json:\"snapshot\"` // filename reference\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **JSONL I/O Patterns**\n\nLocation: `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go`\n\n**Pattern for writing JSONL (one JSON object per line):**\n```go\n// Single entry append\ndata, err := json.Marshal(result)\nif err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"marshaling: %w\", err)\n}\nif _, err := f.Write(append(data, '\\n')); err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"writing: %w\", err)\n}\n\n// Batch write (multiple entries)\nvar sb strings.Builder\nfor _, item := range items {\n    data, err := json.Marshal(item)\n    if err != nil {\n        continue // skip malformed\n    }\n    sb.Write(data)\n    sb.WriteByte('\\n')\n}\nreturn os.WriteFile(path, []byte(sb.String()), 0644)\n```\n\n**Pattern for reading JSONL:**\n```go\ndata, err := os.ReadFile(path)\nif os.IsNotExist(err) {\n    return nil, nil // gracefully handle missing file\n}\nif err != nil {\n    return nil, err\n}\n\nvar items []T\nfor _, line := range strings.Split(strings.TrimSpace(string(data)), \"\\n\") {\n    line = strings.TrimSpace(line)\n    if line == \"\" {\n        continue\n    }\n    var item T\n    if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(line), &item); err != nil {\n        continue // skip malformed lines\n    }\n    items = append(items, item)\n}\nreturn items, nil\n```\n\n**Knowledge base file path convention:**\n```\n.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow-name>.jsonl\n```\n\n### 5. **Test File Conventions**\n\nLocation: Examples from `/workspace/internal/domain/run_test.go`, `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go`, `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go`\n\n**Key patterns:**\n\n1. **Package naming:** Use `<package>_test` suffix\n   ```go\n   package domain_test  // for testing domain package\n   ```\n\n2. **Imports:** Always include testify\n   ```go\n   import (\n       \"testing\"\n       \"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n       \"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n   )\n   ```\n\n3. **Test function naming:** `TestTypeName_Method` or `TestFunctionName`\n   ```go\n   func TestRun_Lifecycle(t *testing.T) { ... }\n   func TestCollectorGathersData(t *testing.T) { ... }\n   ```\n\n4. **Assertion patterns:**\n   - Use `require.*` for critical assertions that should fail fast\n   - Use `assert.*` for supplementary checks\n   ```go\n   require.NoError(t, err)           // fail fast on errors\n   require.Equal(t, expected, actual)\n   assert.Contains(t, content, substring)  // supplementary\n   ```\n\n5. **Temporary directories:** Use `t.TempDir()` for file operations\n   ```go\n   dir := t.TempDir()  // auto-cleaned after test\n   os.MkdirAll(filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\"), 0755)\n   ```\n\n6. **Table-driven tests:** Common pattern for multiple scenarios\n   ```go\n   tests := []struct {\n       name     string\n       input    string\n       expected string\n   }{\n       {\"case1\", \"...\", \"...\"},\n       {\"case2\", \"...\", \"...\"},\n   }\n   for _, tt := range tests {\n       t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n           // test logic\n       })\n   }\n   ```\n\n7. **Mock patterns:** Use interface-based mocking with simple structs\n   ```go\n   type fakeLLM struct {\n       response string\n   }\n   func (f *fakeLLM) Complete(ctx context.Context, system, user string) (string, error) {\n       return f.response, nil\n   }\n   ```\n\n8. **Error handling in tests:**\n   ```go\n   require.Error(t, err)\n   require.NoError(t, err)\n   assert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"expected substring\")\n   ```\n\n### 6. **Fitness Evaluation Specific Patterns**\n\nFrom the evolution design, fitness evaluation should follow these conventions:\n\n1. **JSON struct tags:** Always include JSON tags for serialization\n   ```go\n   type Fitness struct {\n       Score     float64 `json:\"score\"`\n       Details   string  `json:\"details\"`\n       RunID     string  `json:\"run_id\"`\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **JSONL storage:** Fitness records should use JSONL format like knowledge base\n   ```\n   .cloche/evolution/fitness/<workflow-name>.jsonl\n   ```\n\n3. **Error handling:** Graceful degradation pattern\n   ```go\n   if err != nil {\n       return defaultValue, nil  // or log and continue\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **File operations:**\n   - Use `os.OpenFile(path, os.O_APPEND|os.O_CREATE|os.O_WRONLY, 0644)` for appending\n   - Always defer file.Close()\n   - Use filepath.Join for path construction\n\n5. **Context usage:** All I/O should accept and respect `context.Context`\n\n### Absolute File Paths to Key Locations:\n\n1. `/workspace/go.mod` - Module definition\n2. `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run type definition\n3. `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` - Evolution domain types\n4. `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` - JSONL I/O patterns (readKnowledge, writeKnowledge, Log)\n5. `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go` - Data collection pattern\n6. `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go` - Comprehensive test examples\n7. `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go` - Security validation patterns\n8. `/workspace/internal/domain/run_test.go` - Domain test patterns"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5fb6850d040be280 (use SendMessage with to: 'a5fb6850d040be280' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54267\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 37026</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c9bf61f-09a1-44ad-b826-f3dc460a4b97","uuid":"f5aee038-0b4d-42fb-bf33-3cc17c2ec3b0","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:08:23.574Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the project conventions for implementing fitness evaluation. Please find:\n\n1. The domain.Run type definition (look in internal/domain/)\n2. Any existing files in internal/evolution/ directory\n3. The go.mod file to understand module name\n4. Any existing JSONL I/O patterns in the codebase\n5. Test file conventions (how tests are structured)\n\nBe thorough - read the actual file contents for domain types and any evolution files.","agentId":"a5fb6850d040be280","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me compile the comprehensive findings:\n\n## Summary: Project Conventions for Implementing Fitness Evaluation\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase, here are the key conventions and patterns you should follow:\n\n### 1. **Module Name and Imports**\n- **Module:** `github.com/cloche-dev/cloche`\n- **Go version:** 1.25.3\n- **Standard test assertion library:** `github.com/stretchr/testify` (both `assert` and `require`)\n\nFile: `/workspace/go.mod`\n\n### 2. **domain.Run Type Definition**\nLocation: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Core fields:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string                // unique run identifier\n    WorkflowName   string                // which workflow was executed\n    State          RunState               // pending|running